# Phenotype SDK Absorption Plan

> **Status:** scoping / paper exercise
> **Source tree:** `C:\Users\koosh\absorption-staging\phenotype-sdk\`
> **Date:** 2026-07-04
> **Scope:** This plan covers ONLY `phenotype-sdk/`. Sibling trees
> (`absorption-staging/pheno-runtime/` and `absorption-staging/pheno-research-engine/`)
> are out of scope for this document.

---

## 1. Executive Summary

`phenotype-sdk` is the consolidation target for the absorption program.
The tree is a 6-language monorepo that already presents as an SDK-shaped
workspace (`just` tasks per language, `go.work`, `Cargo.toml` workspace
members, `package.json` workspaces, `pyproject.toml` `[tool.uv.workspace]`,
`build.zig`).

**Counts (confirmed by direct read of files):**

| Language | Workspace files | Members | Notes |
|----------|-----------------|---------|-------|
| Python | `pyproject.toml` (uv) + `uv.lock` + `justfile` | **16** top-level dirs under `lang/python/packages/` (`+1` for `mcp/agentmcp` aliased) | 4 are umbrella kits with sub-packages inside `python/` AND `rust/` |
| Rust | `Cargo.toml` workspace + `ORIGIN.md` + `README.md` | **17** direct crates + **1 sub-workspace** `pheno-runtime/crates/*` with **5** sub-crates + **17** Rust crates nested inside 4 Python umbrella kits | **Total Rust crates to absorb ≈ 17 + 5 + 17 = 39** |
| TypeScript | `package.json` (`name: phenotype-sdk-ts`, `workspaces: [packages/*]`) + `tsconfig.json` | **0** (packages/ dir absent) | Empty workspace — only root metadata |
| Zig | `build.zig` (static + executable) | **1** (`packages/phenotype-core/`) | Tiny stub |
| Go | `go.work` + `go.mod` + `justfile` | **10** packages under `lang/go/packages/` + 1 `okf/manifest.okf.yaml` + docs scaffolding | Only `packages/devhex` is the active module (per `go.work`); other 9 are stubs/deferred per ADR-011 |
| Mojo | `README.md` only | **0** | Stub |

**Total non-empty artifacts to absorb: ~62 units** (16 Python pkgs + 39 Rust crates + 1 Zig crate + ~10 Go modules + 0 TS + 0 Mojo + the justfile/Cargo.toml/pyproject.toml/build.zig/go.work/tsconfig.json scaffolding + `docs/`, `okf/`, `okf/wiki`, `mcp/agentmcp`).

---

## 2. Verdict

**Staged absorption — DO NOT attempt in a single PR.** Absorbing all
six language workspaces atomically would:

- Touch every Python umbrella-kit (`DataKit`, `ObservabilityKit`,
  `ResilienceKit`, `TestingKit`, `AuthKit`, `McpKit`) plus four
  `phenotype-*` Rust-utility repos and the new monorepos
  (`phenotype-python-sdk`, `phenotype-go-sdk`).
- Mix unrelated concerns: data-plane primitives (Rust crates),
  runtime containers (`pheno-runtime` sub-workspace), observability
  stacks, AI/ML infra (`pheno-minio`, `pheno-nats`, `phenotype-llm`,
  `phenotype-surrealdb`), and stack umbrellas (data-kit, observability-kit).
- Move `pheno-runtime` (an edition-2024 sub-workspace with bun.lock,
  Cargo.lock, justfile, kitty-specs/) into a location the destination
  monorepo is not shaped to hold.

**Recommend a 3-phase campaign:**

- **Phase 1 — Rust scaffold (PR-1, most surgical).** Fold the 17
  `lang/rust/packages/*` crates into a destination Rust workspace
  (see §5.1). Defer the 17 crates hidden inside Python umbrellas
  and the 5 `pheno-runtime` sub-crates.
- **Phase 2 — Python unification (PR-2).** Mirror the `lang/python/`
  monorepo into `phenotype-python-sdk` namespace. The
  `[tool.uv.workspace] members = [...]` block in
  `lang/python/pyproject.toml:61-91` is already pre-wired; copying
  the toml + `uv.lock` + `justfile` should be the main payload.
- **Phase 3 — TS / Zig / Mojo / Go stubs (PR-3, lowest risk).** These
  four workspaces are mostly empty; preserve as-is, declare workspace
  roots only, and require zero source movement.

