### 4.3 TypeScript landing — destination: `phenotype-ts` (NEW monorepo) or attach to `phenoXdd` / `phenotype-auth-ts`

The `lang/ts/` workspace is empty. Recommend creating **no new packages** in this PR and just preserving the workspace root files in a sibling location. Concrete options:

| Option | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| 4.3.a Land as `phenotype-ts-sdk` new mono | Clean ownership | No content yet — over-weight |
| 4.3.b Bundle into `phenoXdd` as `packages/phenotype-sdk-ts` | Reuses existing TS | Off-topic |
| 4.3.c Keep in `phenotype-sdk/lang/ts/` | No movement | Doesn't reduce the staging footprint |

**Recommendation: 4.3.c (keep as-is) for Phase 3** — there is literally no source to absorb.

### 4.4 Zig landing — destination: `phenotype-zig-sdk` (NEW monorepo) or keep in-place

Same as TS — only one stub crate. Recommended: 4.3.c/4.4.c (keep in-place).

### 4.5 Go landing — destination: `phenotype-go-sdk` (already exists in fleet)

| Source | Destination |
|---|---|
| `lang/go/go.work` | `phenotype-go-sdk/go.work` |
| `lang/go/go.mod` | root or merge with `phenotype-go-sdk/go.mod` |
| `lang/go/go.work.sum` | merge |
